data.title: Executive Women of the Palm Beaches Foundation, Inc
data.meta_description: Executive Women of the Palm Beaches (EWPBF) is an organization of empowered, accomplished, professional women. We provide peer support, intellectual stimulation and connections that enhance the executive careers and personal lives of our members.
data.meta_site_name: Executive Women of the Palm Beaches Foundation, Inc
data.text:
The EW 1982 Society was formed to support the legacy of the Executive Women of the Palm Beaches Foundation. The name EW 1982 Society is in homage to the year that EWPBF was founded.

The goal is to support EWPBFâ€™s operational needs and the future growth, while ensuring its sustainability to serve its mission of helping women succeed and lead.

Learn More

Connecting and giving back to women and girls in our community are at the heart of everything we do at Executive Women of the Palm Beaches. We support women of all ages attending Palm Beach Atlantic University, Keiser University, Palm Beach State College and Florida Atlantic University.

Learn More

Cynthia Allen Gracey was the first President of EWPBF in 1982. Over 40 years later we are proud to have had 39 leaders who guided the way for our members and the organization to not only succeed but thrive. Vicki Pugh is the current president. 12 additional women serve on the 2024-2025 board of directors.
